How to use this file
	1.	Replace the placeholder line at the top with the correct copyright year and owner. Example:

Copyright (c) 2025 Your Name or Company

	2.	Save the file as LICENSE in the root of your repository.
	3.	Commit & push (example commands):

# create LICENSE file locally (if not using a web editor)
echo "(paste the text from this file)" > LICENSE
# or open an editor and save

# then commit and push
git add LICENSE
git commit -m "Add MIT license"
git push origin main

Replace main with your default branch name if different.

